nd the West. Professor Smith first describes Vietnamese political and social traditions and shows how they were challenged by the West after 1858. He examines Viet-Nam's search for independence and modernization in the first half of this century, contrasts the two governments of the partitioned country during the years 1954-1963, and stresses the critical need to reassess attitudes toward Viet-Nam. His sophisticated, ambitious survey of Viet-Nam history will have a lasting value that sets it apart from the scores of ephemeral books on this country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAsian Studies. 4aMilitary History. 4aVietnam. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh1 aFox, Diane Niblack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Marc Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKukk, Christopher L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLessard, Micheline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOstrowski, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuinn-Judge, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson, C.Michele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWehrle, Edmund F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilcox, Wynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilcox, Wynn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171164040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978150